/*
 * This Hyperlambda snippet pauses the execution of the current thread for a specified duration.
 * The sleep duration is defined in milliseconds, allowing the thread to release control back to the operating system.
 *
 * 1. [sleep]
 *    * Pauses the current thread for 1000 milliseconds, equivalent to 1 second.
 *    * This operation is non-blocking, as it releases the thread back to the OS during the sleep period.
 */
sleep:1000